<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-6577] IPC server response buffer reset threshold should be configurable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6577</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-6460&quot; title=&quot;Ignore stale and decommissioned nodes in NetworkTopology#sortByDistance&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HDFS-6460&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HDFS-6460&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the response buffers in o.a.h.ipc.Server.Handler was reset when the buffer grows beyond max size of 1MB. This frees heap from large responses occupying it. This max response size limit should be configurable. Details in subsequent comment.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12456739">HADOOP-6577</key>
            <summary>IPC server response buffer reset threshold should be configurable</summary>
